  "body": "<p>My cousins gave me this adorable Hallmark card for the baby shower and I found the perfect way to save it for Project Life.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/db426858361d258f.jpg?v=1782530405\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>I simply used the 3x4 We R Memory Keepers punch (which was available at Studio Calico and <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/we-r-memory-keepers-inc/143758-3x4-card-punch/\">Two Peas in a Bucket)</a> - just click Notify Me to be alerted when back in stock. The punch is easy to use, but I must admit takes a bit of muscle. I like to put it on a solid table (preferably a low table - that isn't a high countertop) and push both my palms (and arms) into it.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/0815c42649c3f75f.jpg?v=1782530408\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/df1e6107b45dc21a.jpg?v=1782530411\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>I saved the inside of the card with the hand written message, but love that this part can live inside of one of my Project Life pockets. </p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
}